\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. S. spontaneum} L., {\i Mantissa Alt.} 183 (1771). Tall rhizomatous perennial; stems 2-4 m or more. Leaf-blades mostly 5-15 mm wide. Panicle 25-60 cm, the axis hirsute; racemes 3-15 cm, usually much longer than the supporting branches. Spikelets 3·5-7 mm, the callus with silky white hairs 2-3 times as long as the spikelet; glumes membranous above, subcoriaceous in the lower third, glabrous on the back, ciliate above; upper lemma subulate and up to 3 mm or absent.{\i  Moist  soils. Sicilia.} Si. ({\i S. Asia, N. & E. Africa.})
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. S. officinarum} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 54 (1753). Like {\b 1} but leaf-blades up to 40 mm wide; panicle 100 cm or more, broadly pyramidal, the axis glabrous to pubescent.{\i  Cultivated in S. Spain} ({\i sugar-cane}). [Hs.] ({\i New Guinea; widely cultivated in the tropics and subtropics.})
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. S. ravennae} (L.) Murray,{\i  Syst. Veg.} 88 (1774) ({\i Erianthus ravennae} (L.) Beauv.). Caespitose perennial; stems up to 3 m. Panicle 25-60 cm, narrowly ovate, plumose, lobed; racemes 1-2 cm, much shorter than the flexuous supporting branches. Spikelets 3·5-5 mm, the callus-hairs about as long as the spikelet; lower glume membranous, hirsute on the back or glabrous, attenuate to an acute apex; upper lemma 2·5-3 mm, lanceolate, hyaline, with a terminal awn 3-4 mm.{\i  By water and on coastal sands. Mediterranean region; S.W. & E. Bulgaria.} Al Bl Bu Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Si Tu [Rm].
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. S. strictum} (Host) Sprengel, {\i Pugillus }2: 16 (1815) ({\i Erianthus hostii} Griseb.). Caespitose perennial; stems up to 2 m. Panicle 10-25 cm, linear to lanceolate, dense; racemes 2-6 cm, about as long as the stiff supporting branches, appressed to the axis. Spikelets 4·5-5·5 mm, the callus-hairs about as long as the spikelet; lower glume cartilaginous, purplish, glabrous on the back, hirsute on the margin, abruptly contracted to an obtuse or subacute apex; upper lemma 3-4 mm, lanceolate, with a terminal awn 2-6 mm.{\i  Damp sands and stony streamsides. Balkan peninsula, extending to N.E. Italy and S. Romania.} Al Bu Gr It Ju Rm Tu.
